                                        <h1 class="h1">React Events</h1>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="pt-2 min-vh-100">
                                        <p>If you have coded even a little bit in javascript, you know the importance of events.&nbsp;</p>
                                        <h2>Events</h2>
                                        <p>Every HTML attribute in React is written in camelCase syntax. Event is also an attribute. Hence, written in camelCase.</p>
                                        <p>As we learnt variables, states, javascript operations are written in curly braces {}, same is true with React event handlers too! Like this: onClick={show}&nbsp;</p>
                                        <div class="text-white bg-black bg-light p-3 border rounded">
                                            <pre>&lt;button onClick=&#123;show&#125;&gt;Show&lt;/button&gt;</pre>
                                        </div>
                                        <h2>Arguments in events</h2>
                                        <p>We can't pass arguments just like that, it will give syntax error. First, we need to put the whole function in arrow function, like this:</p>
                                        <div class="text-white bg-black bg-light p-3 border rounded">
                                            <pre><code>&lt;button onClick=&#123; () =&gt; show('true') &#125;&gt;Show&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>
                                        </div>
                                        <h2>React Event Object</h2>
                                        <p>Event handler can be provided to the function like this:</p>
                                        <div class="text-white bg-black bg-light p-3 border rounded">
                                            <pre><code>&lt;button onClick=&#123; (event) =&gt; show('true', event) &#125;&gt;Show&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@popperjs/core@2.11.6/dist/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
